				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">No clue on which AAs to get<a name="32924"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 10:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been busting levels, and haven't really focused on AAs much.  I just got level 65 the other day, and have my little buffer of experience, so I'm switching to 100 percent AAs exp. 
<br />

<br />
I am primarily a grouping bard, usually in LDON.  I also raid a couple times a week, usually Tier 2 Planes.  I do not solo at all, so I don't feel the need for a godawful mana pool for charming.  I know that FM uses mana. I have FT1.
<br />

<br />
The only AAs I currently have are Innate Run Speed 3 and Innate Regeneration 3 from General Abilities.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure if I should save up next for Fading Memories.  It doesn't seem to have any pre-requirements for it, and it sounds so very useful.
<br />

<br />
Or should I work on my Archetype Abilities, and maybe get Channeling Focus, Combat Agility, or Mental Clarity?
<br />

<br />
Or am I completely overlooking something else that will really help me/
<br />

<br />
Thank you for your advice.  I rely on this community a great deal.
<br />
</span></td>
