				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: No clue on which AAs to get<a name="32985"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 2:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A blank slate eh?  If it was me, I would do..
<br />
FM
<br />
IM3
<br />
ND3
<br />
CA1
<br />
CS1
<br />
PE
<br />
Bellow
<br />
SM3
<br />
JF3
<br />
CA3
<br />
LR5
<br />

<br />
That outta take you a few months lol!
<br />

<br />
This is based on the following assumptions:
<br />
You pull a lot.  FM is a defining ability for bards, it is such a useful too, you wont know how you made it to 65 without it sometimes.  It can change a lot for ya.
<br />

<br />
You value your song effects above your offensive melee abilities.  IM3 will let you be the best bard you can be with most intsruments, or without!
<br />

<br />
You like being alive ;o)  ND3, and PE will get you a LOT more HPs with the same gear you are using now.  PE will get you even more.  I say get CA1 and CS1 cause it's cheap, and PE will make em even better.
<br />

<br />
I put bellow next because it is a great pulling tool, very handy.
<br />

<br />
Then I ranked SM3 cause at 65 your normal LDoN twist will be voice based, SM3 will really effect the resists and DS on POV.
<br />

<br />
JF3 will make most songs even more powerful
<br />

<br />
Then CA and LR because imho, Avoidance &gt; Mitigation.  I went all out Avoidance, now Im working on offensive melee AAs, I will cap out mitigation when I cap out Offensive AAs.
<br />

<br />
Good luck, and remember, its not what AAs you have, its how you use what you DO have ;o)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
